Third Party Actions

Example of using a thrid party actions: 

name: My NPM package workflow
on:
  push:

jobs:
  node-20-release:
  runs-on: ubuntu-latest
  steps:
    - uses: actions/setup-node@v3 # this is using an official GitHub action (as noted by "actions/")
      with:
        node-version: 20
    - run: npm ci
    - run: npm test
    - run: npm publish

Why you want to use third pary actions: 
- Avoids repetitive and extensive commands, and keeps things DRY. 
- Can be configured via the "with" k:v pair. Makes flexible and reusable. 
- Can be compbined with other steps. Can be used to encapsulate setup tasks before running other commands. 
- Can create your own actions for public or private use. 

GitHub Action Marketplace: 
- https://github.com/marketplace?type=actions
- You should mostly focus on actions that are by verified creators. 
